AWS Storage Services:
EBS - Elastic Block Store --> Storage for EC2 instance, root volume, Database --> SSD
S3 --> Simple Storage Service --> HDD, cheaper than EBS
EFS --> Elastic File Storage --> 3x costlier than EBS

https://docs.aws.amazon.com/ebs/latest/userguide/ebs-volume-types.html

mount a volume to EC2 instance
sudo su -
df -h
lsblk
fdisk -l
mkfs.ext4 /dev/xvdf
mkdir /mount-point1
mount /dev/xvdf /mount-point1/
lsblk
cd /mount-point1/


